{"type":"message","id":"3ce814fd","parentId":"f85f4c1e","timestamp":"2026-02-28T14:01:37.715Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call-828dcfcc-41c0-4783-adce-f5aa4c5f8854","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/kero/.openclaw/workspace/skills/self-improving-agent/SKILL.md","limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"arcee-ai/trinity-large-preview:free","usage":{"input":18331,"output":38,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18369,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772287294145}}
{"type":"message","id":"5bbed657","parentId":"3ce814fd","timestamp":"2026-02-28T14:01:37.727Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call-828dcfcc-41c0-4783-adce-f5aa4c5f8854","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: self-improvement\ndescription: \"Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude ('No, that's wrong...', 'Actually...'), (3) User requests a capability that doesn't exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.\"\nmetadata:\n---\n\n# Self-Improvement Skill\n\nLog learnings and errors to markdown files for continuous improvement. Coding agents can later process these into fixes, and important learnings get promoted to project memory.\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n| Situation | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Command/operation fails | Log to `.learnings/ERRORS.md` |\n| User corrects you | Log to `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` with category `correction` |\n| User wants missing feature | Log to `.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md` |\n| API/external tool fails | Log to `.learnings/ERRORS.md` with integration details |\n| Knowledge was outdated | Log to `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` with category `knowledge_gap` |\n| Found better approach | Log to `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` with category `best_practice` |\n| Simplify/Harden recurring patterns | Log/update `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` with `Source: simplify-and-harden` and a stable `Pattern-Key` |\n| Similar to existing entry | Link with `**See Also**`, consider priority bump |\n| Broadly applicable learning | Promote to `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and/or `.github/copilot-instructions.md` |\n| Workflow improvements | Promote to `AGENTS.md` (OpenClaw workspace) |\n| Tool gotchas | Promote to `TOOLS.md` (OpenClaw workspace) |\n| Behavioral patterns | Promote to `SOUL.md` (OpenClaw workspace) |\n\n## OpenClaw Setup (Recommended)\n\nOpenClaw is the primary platform for this skill. It uses workspace-based prompt injection with automatic skill loading.\n\n### Installation\n\n**Via ClawdHub (recommended):**\n```bash\nclawdhub install self-improving-agent\n```\n\n**Manual:**\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/peterskoett/self-improving-agent.git ~/.openclaw/skills/self-improving-agent\n```\n\nRemade for openclaw from original repo : https://github.com/pskoett/pskoett-ai-skills - https://github.com/pskoett/pskoett-ai-skills/tree/main/skills/self-improvement\n\n### Workspace Structure\n\nOpenClaw injects these files into every session:\n\n```\n\n[598 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772287297724}}
{"type":"message","id":"c22395f2","parentId":"5bbed657","timestamp":"2026-02-28T14:01:52.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The self-improving-agent skill helps you get better over time by:\n\n## What it does\n- **Logs errors** when commands fail or tools don't work\n- **Captures corrections** when you tell me I'm wrong\n- **Tracks feature requests** for things I can't do yet\n- **Records knowledge gaps** when my information is outdated\n- **Documents best practices** when I find better ways to do things\n\n## Why it matters\nInstead of forgetting mistakes, it turns them into:\n- **Fixes** for recurring problems\n- **Skills** that can be reused in other projects\n- **Documentation** that prevents future errors\n- **Automation** for workflows I learn\n\n## How it works\nEvery time something goes wrong or you correct me, it logs it to `.learnings/` files. Then it can:\n- **Promote** important learnings to permanent project memory\n- **Create new skills** from proven solutions\n- **Help other sessions** learn from past mistakes\n- **Improve itself** over time\n\n## Example\nIf I try to run `npm install` but your project uses `pnpm`, it logs that error. Next time, it'll know to use `pnpm install` automatically.\n\nIt's like having a memory that gets smarter with every session instead of starting fresh each time."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"arcee-ai/trinity-large-preview:free","usage":{"input":18949,"output":271,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19220,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772287297728}}
